org.apache.derbyTesting.perf.clients

Class SingleRecordFiller

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.derbyTesting.perf.clients.SingleRecordFiller
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DBFiller

    public class SingleRecordFiller
extends java.lang.Object
implements DBFiller
    Class which generates and populates tables that can be used by SingleRecordSelectClient and SingleRecordUpdateClient. This tables contain rows with an int column (id) and a varchar(100) column (text). The id column is declared as primary key.

      • SingleRecordFiller

        public SingleRecordFiller(int records,
                          int tables)
        Generate a filler that creates the specified number of tables, each of which contains the specified number of records. When this constructor is used, the table only contains two columns: a primary key column (INT) and a text column (VARCHAR(100)).
        Parameters:
        records - the number of records in each table
        tables - the number of tables to create

      • SingleRecordFiller

                          boolean withSecIndex,
                          boolean withNonIndexed)
        Generate a filler that creates the specified number of tables, each of which contains the specified number of records.
        Parameters:
        records - the number of records in each table
        tables - the number of tables to create
        type - which SQL type to store the text as (one of java.sql.Types.VARCHAR, java.sql.Types.BLOB and java.sql.Types.CLOB.
